<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-05T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-05T23:00:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.20/632a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-06T00:00:00-04:00">May 6,
                                    1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1445. The Combined Chiefs of Staff yesterday evening approved the War
                            Department recommendations for the BEF, including dates for movement of
                            the first contingents. This would be very soon.</p>
                        <p>The War Department asks that we keep in mind that absolute secrecy of
                            sailing dates is essential to security.</p>
                        <p>General Leitão de Carvalho<note n="56" xml:id="d529fn56">Senior Brazilian
                                member of the Joint Brazil–United States Defense Commission.</note>
                            was the first to be informed last night.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>